KubSTU CTF 2026 - OSINT Writeup
----------------------------------------------------------------
Challenge: City that doesn't exist (928 points)
Category:  OSINT
Author:    @borsch_krd
----------------------------------------------------------------

OBJECTIVE
----------------------------------------------------------------
Identify the Russian legal entity that managed a children's
themed park (a licensed clone of a foreign concept) in a major
southern Russian mall, and find the date that entity submitted
a trademark application through Rospatent (Russia's IP registry).

Flag format: KubSTU{INN_of_management_company_DD.MM.YYYY}

----------------------------------------------------------------

TOOLS USED
----------------------------------------------------------------
1. Yandex / Bing - initial park identification
2. TMview (tmdn.org) - international trademark database search
3. FIPS / Rospatent (fips.ru) - Russian trademark registry
4. rusprofile.ru - Russian company registry lookup
5. biglion.ru - deal platform (revealed the managing entity)

----------------------------------------------------------------

STEPS
----------------------------------------------------------------

Step 1 - Identify the park and mall
   The challenge title "City that doesn't exist" and the clue
   "licensed clone of a foreign concept" pointed to a KidZania-
   style children's city-of-professions park. Searched for such
   parks in Krasnodar (home of KubSTU, southern Russia).

   Search: "детский город профессий Краснодар ОЗ Молл"

   Found: MINOPOLIS - an interactive children's park at
   OZ Mall (ул. Крылатая, 2, Краснодар, 3rd floor).
   The concept originates from Austria/Belgium (KCC
   Entertainment Design). In 2019, it renamed to ZkidZ City.
   This matches all challenge conditions.

   [Image: Challenge description screenshot]


Step 2 - Find the trademark submission in Rospatent
   Searched TMview (tmdn.org) for "MINOPOLIS".
   Found a Russian Federation trademark:
     - Name:        MINOPOLIS
     - App number:  2018756480
     - App date:    20/12/2018
     - Status:      Registered
     - Owner:       Минополис Уорлдуайд Эдьютейнмент ЛЛК

   Confirmed via FIPS record RU723853:
     (210) Application number: 2018756480
     (220) Application submission date: 20.12.2018
     (151) Date of state registration: 19.08.2019
     Rights holder: Minopolis Worldwide Education LLC
                    (Delaware, USA)

   Filing date confirmed: 20.12.2018

   [Image: FIPS official record RU723853 showing submission date]


Step 3 - Find the Russian management company INN
   The original ТПКО Минополис Краснодар (INN 2312196680) was
   liquidated October 2014 but the park ran until 2019. A
   successor operated it.

   Found the answer via a Biglion.ru deal listing for
   Minopolis (October 2018). The terms of service stated:

     "Tickets are paid according to the price list of
      ООО «Детство+». ООО «Детство+» has the right to
      refuse coupon activation."

   Looked up ООО "Детство+" on rusprofile.ru:
     Full name: ООО "ДЕТСТВО +"
     INN:       2312206762
     OGRN:      1132312009719
     Address:   Краснодар, Крылатая ул., д. 2 (OZ Mall)
     Activity:  Entertainment and recreational activities
     Registered: 16.09.2013
     Liquidated: 23.04.2021 (by reorganization/merger)

   Perfect match: same address as Minopolis, active during
   the trademark filing period, entertainment activity.

   [Image: rusprofile listing showing ООО "Детство+" INN 2312206762
           at Krylata 2 address]


----------------------------------------------------------------

KEY TAKEAWAY
----------------------------------------------------------------
The trick was that the original company (ТПКО Минополис) was
already dissolved in 2014, but a different entity (ООО Детство+)
had been operating the park since 2013. The management company
was revealed not through EGRUL searches, but through a third-
party deal platform's legal fine print (Biglion). The trademark
was filed by the US-based franchisor in December 2018, right
before the 2019 rebrand to ZkidZ.

